AUDIO: 'Most developers are over-engineering internal tools, and let\'s face it, we all know it. You spin up React, wire APIs, build off, manage state just to ship a dashboard that\'s basically forms and tables. This is Appsmith, an open-source tool with over 39,000 stars'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that can replace most of that in just minutes. Think of it as the open-source alternative to Bubble, and I\'ll show you how it works in just a few minutes. Now, Appsmith isn\'t brand new, but it'

[00:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'still doesn\'t get talked about as often as it should. It\'s built not for landing pages or customer apps, just internal tools. We get UI you can drag and drop, but with full JavaScript, so you\'re'

[00:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'never stuck. You connect databases, APIs, SaaS tools, and you still use Git like a normal dev. Now, there\'s no lock-in here, and we can fully self-host it for free, plus we get unlimited users. So, the real question'

[00:56] [scene:talk]
