AUDIO: 'it\'s done. Add a trigger to our button to update, maybe a toast notification. Click deploy, and that\'s a working CRUD app. I mean, okay, super basic, as I\'m hitting on all this in just a couple minutes, but I know you can see the real versatility behind all this and how fast'

[02:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this would be in a workflow, too. No React setup, no API layer, no auth wiring. This took maybe a minute, maybe two, okay? And you still have full control with JavaScript, themes, and Git. So, yeah. It\'s free, it\'s fast, so'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'no paying for Bubble or something else. This is a great tool to spin up quickly. Appsmith is basically UI on one side, data on the other, and JavaScript for connecting everything. Widgets handle'

[02:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your UI, data sources connect to databases, APIs, even LLMs, and queries are just SQL, REST, or JavaScript. And the key idea is JavaScript is everywhere. Now, most low-code tools'

[02:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'hide logic from you, and then one exposes it. And that\'s why devs are switching. Git works the way you expect, branching, merging, CI/CD. There\'s nothing weird, and you can self-host with Docker or Kubernetes. So, you'

[03:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'control your data and your costs. You can build custom components with React or plain JavaScript, and it\'s production-ready with RBAC, audit logs, and SSO just built-in. Now, with all'

